{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}
The '''1984 Bhiwandi riot''' occurred in May 1984 in and around [[Bhiwandi]] town in [[India]]n state of [[Maharashtra]]. It left 146 people dead and over 600 injured.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=RGyO0E86X1oC&pg=PA87&dq=bhiwandi+riots+1984+May&hl=en&sa=X&ei=s7DpT53ZB6GDmQWA0pH6DQ&ved=0CEgQuwUwAw#v=onepage&q=bhiwandi%20riots%201984%20May&f=false]</ref>  <ref>{{cite news |title=Bhiwandi riots: Four held from Malegaon|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/bhiwandi-riots-four-held-from-malegaon/8858/ |publisher=[[Indian Express]] |date= 20 Jul 2006 }}</ref> On 17 May 1984, riots broke out in industrial belt from [[Bombay]], [[Thane]], and [[Bhiwandi]] after a saffron flag was placed at the top of a mosque. In all, 278 were killed and 1,118 were wounded.<ref>{{harvnb|Hansen|2001|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=-y3iNt0djbQC&printsec=frontcover#PPA77,M1 77]|Ref=bhi84}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Communal Riots in Post-independence India|author=Asgharali Engineer |authorlink= Asgharali Engineer|publisher= Universities Press|year= 1991|isbn=8173701024 |page=330 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yB5NM0o3I9QC&pg=PA330&lpg=PA330&dq=1984+Bhiwandi+riot&source=bl&ots=CfLcGchujL&sig=RBUIoTlk-4WCkbJkgUG4hKntIpg&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Nf3rT5GyBYXtrAekrMDRBQ&ved=0CF8Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=1984%20Bhiwandi%20riot&f=false |ref= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book
|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-y3iNt0djbQC&printsec=frontcover|last=Hansen|first=Thomas Blom|title=Wages of Violence: Naming and Identity in Postcolonial Bombay|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-0-691-08840-2|year=2001|accessdate=13 November 2008|ref=bhi84|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>

