{{Infobox Convention | name = Anime South | image = | caption = | status = Inactive | venue = Hampton Inn Pensacola Beach | location = [[Pensacola, Florida]] | country = United States | first = 2005 | last = 2013 | organizer = | attendance = 972 in 2009<ref name="AC-2009a"/> | website = http://www.animesouth.com/ }}
'''Anime South''' was a three-day [[anime convention]] held in the city of [[Pensacola, Florida]]. The convention also has the distinction of being the first anime convention to garner its [[seed money]] from a small number of contributors who desired an anime convention in the area.
==Programming== Anime South hosted many events common to other anime conventions, such as anime screenings, panels and workshops, game shows, dealers room, artist alley, video game room, dance, and cosplay events.<ref name="dl2006b">{{Citation | last1 = Holt | first1 = Keri | title = Anime fans up to speed on dating scene | newspaper = The Destin Log | date = 2006-11-15 | url = }}</ref>
==History== Anime South was created by one of the co-founders of [[Anime USA]]. Planning took place over a two-month period, after which the largest luxury hotel in the region, The Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa, was contracted for November 18–20, 2005.{{citation needed|date=April 2008}} The 2015 event was cancelled due to financial issues.<ref name="AC-2015">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/5477/anime-south-2015 | title = Anime South 2015 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2018-10-03}}</ref>
