{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}} The [[War on Terror]] is the campaign launched by the United States of America in response to the [[September 11 attacks]] against organizations designated with terrorism.<ref>{{cite book|last=Combs|first=Cindy C.|author2=Slann, Martin |title=Encyclopedia of Terrorism|publisher=Infobase Publishing|location=New York NY|year=2007|pages=417–424|isbn=0-8160-6277-3}}</ref><ref name="hs">{{cite web|url=http://www.iwar.org.uk/homesec/resources/war-on-terror/timeline.pdf|title=Homeland Security: War on Terror Timeline|accessdate=April 3, 2010}}</ref> The campaign, whose stated objective was eliminating international terrorism, began in 2001.<ref name="WH 10-07-01">{{cite press release|publisher=The White House|date=October 7, 2001|title=Presidential Address to the Nation|url=https://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2001/10/print/20011007-8.html}}</ref> The following is a '''timeline''' of events linked to the '''War on Terror'''. {{Expand list|date=April 2010}}
