har Province]], Afghanistan, but he evaded them and later escaped into Pakistan, however, 200 al-Qaeda and Taliban fighters were killed. |- style="background:white" |December 10 |In [[Iraqi Kurdistan]], the two splinter groups that broke off from [[Kurdistan Islamic Movement|Islamic Movement of Kurdistan (IMK)]] that formed Jund al-Islam became [[Ansar al-Islam|Ansar al-Islam (AAI)]].<ref name="Chalk, Peter 2012">Chalk, Peter, Encyclopedia of Terrorism Volume 1, 2012, ABC-CLIO</ref> |- style="background:white" |December 18 |[[Transit Center at Manas#Operation Enduring Freedom|Operation Enduring Freedom – Kyrgyzstan]] begins.<ref>[[Daniel P. Bolger]], Why we lost: A general's inside account of the Iraq and Afghanistan wars, 2014, xiii</ref> |}
