ilitary Airbase. Between 397–423 terrorists, rebels and militants were killed whilst 161 Pro-Government forces and Syrian Democratic Forces were killed. |- style="background:khaki" |February 2–20 |The [[Southern Abyan Offensive (2016)]] takes place: AQAP terrorists succeeded in uniting its western and eastern parts of its Emirate in Yemen, marking the beginning of the [[Abyan conflict (2016-2017)|Abyan Governorate clashes]]. |- style="background:khaki" |February 2–May 22 |The [[Siege of Fallujah (2016)]] takes place: As part of the Anbar campaign (2015–16), Iraqi and Iranian forces, supported by the coalition, surrounded a besieged the ISIL-held city of Fallujah, (the [[Battle of Fallujah (2014)|city fell to ISIL]] and other militants during their offensive in Al Anbar Governorate in 2014) to pave way for an eventual assault on the city. Over at least 520 terrorists were killed, over 180 Iraqi tribesmen were captured. |- style="background:khaki" |February 9 |The Battle of Ramadi (2015–16) ends after Iraqi government forces, Shia milita and Sunni tribal forces, with coalition support after successfully liberating the city as part of the Anbar campaign (2015–16) in Iraq, from ISIL occupation, killing at least over 350 terrorists whilst the combined force lost between 150 and over 297 killed and over 1,000 wounded. |- style="background:lightgreen" |February 14–March 6 |The [[Nangarhar Offensive (2016)|Nangarhar Offensive]] takes place: Afghan forces supported by [[Resolute Support Mission|RSM]] troops and U.S. airstrikes in particular, carried out an operation ISIL-KP terrorists in Nangarhar Province, Afghanistan. The offensive was a success, confining and almost eliminating ISIL-KP from the Province, killing at least 200 terrorists. |- style="background:yellowgreen" |Early March |Indonesian security forces began [[Operation Tinombala]] in Indonesia against the [[Mujahidin Indonesia Timur|Mujahidin Indonesia Timur (MIT/EIM)]] – an Islamic terrorist group that pledged a